com.SCHSRobotics.HAL9001.util.control

Class AutoTransitioner

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • com.SCHSRobotics.HAL9001.util.control.AutoTransitioner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class AutoTransitioner
extends Thread
    Created by KNO3 Robotics AutoTransitioner is a utility to automatically initialize the teleop program of your choice after the autonomous period ends. To use AutoTransitioner, go to your OpMode/LinearOpMode, and place the following line of code in your init() method or before your waitForStart() (for OpMode and LinearOpMode, respectively): AutoTransitioner.transitionOnStop(this, "MainRobot Teleop"); Where 'MainRobot Teleop' is replaced with the NAME of your teleop program. See full documentation on kno3.net/resources for more info.
